1. Random Numbers
In the original daemons multi-spin coding method [11] that we have adapted (and modified), the thermal bath is represented by the two daemon-bits d0 and d1 that form a two-bits integer s = d0 + 2 ∗ d1. Hence, Ito and Kanada

